GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 894
Short Title: NC A&T Chancellor's Residence Transfer. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Robinson (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
April 30, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO CONVEY CERTAIN REAL PROPERTY ON WHICH IS SITUATED THE
3 NORTH CAROLINA AGRICULTURAL AND TECHNICAL STATE UNIVERSITY
4 CHANCELLOR'S RESIDENCE.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) The State of North Carolina shall convey to The North Carolina
7 A&T Real Estate Foundation, Inc. (the Grantee), for consideration of one dollar ($1.00), all its
8 rights, titles, and interests in the parcel identified with Land Asset ID 1128 in the inventory of
9 State-owned land maintained by the Department of Administration pursuant to G.S. 143-341.
10 This is the same property identified with PIN Number 7866-15-4390, as seen in the Office of the
11 Tax Administrator in Guilford County, and is described in Deed Book 4884, Page 1816 in the
12 Guilford County Register of Deeds.
13 SECTION 1.(b) In the event that the Grantee sells the real property described in this
14 section, the Grantee shall use the proceeds of the sale for the purchase of a new Chancellor's
15 residence for the North Carolina Agricultural and Technical State University.
16 SECTION 2. The State of North Carolina shall convey the real property described
17 in Section 1 of this act "as is" and "where is" without warranty. The State makes no
18 representations or warranties concerning the title to the property, the boundaries of the property,
19 the uses to which the property may be put, zoning, local ordinances, or any physical,
20 environmental, health, and safety conditions relating to the property.
21 SECTION 3. The conveyance of the State's rights, titles, and interests in the real
22 property described in Section 1 of this act shall be exempt from the provisions of Article 7 of
23 Chapter 146 of the General Statutes. The conveyance shall comply with the provisions of Article
24 16 of Chapter 146 of the General Statutes, provided that the provisions of G.S. 146-74 shall not
25 apply.
26 SECTION 4. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
27 Administration the sum of five thousand dollars ($5,000) in nonrecurring funds for the
28 2025-2026 fiscal year to offset the costs to the Department for the real estate transaction
29 described in this act.
30 SECTION 5. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*S894-v-1*

